{DIALOGUE}: Hurry up.
{DIALOGUE}: It's about you... I mean sort of...Come on!
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 37 INT. BIG BOB'S/BREAK ROOM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nancy guides Sarah to the small black and white portable TV in the corner.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Two other girls, smoking cigarettes with their shoes off and nyloned feet on the table, are already watching.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: One glances at Sarah.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WAITRESS
{DIALOGUE}: Hey, Sarah.
{DIALOGUE}: This is weird.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They huddle around the set, intent on a newscast in progress.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TV ANCHORWOMAN
{DIALOGUE}: ...and a police spokesman at the scene refused to speculate on a motive for the execution- style slaying of the Encino housewife.
{DIALOGUE}: He did however say that an accurate description of the suspect has been compiled from several witnesses.
{DIALOGUE}: Once again, Sarah Connor, thirty-five, mother of two, brutally shot to death in her home this afternoon.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As the news grinds on, Sarah gazes unseeingly at the screen.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nancy claps her on the shoulder, laughing.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NANCY
{DIALOGUE}: You're dead, honey.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 38 EXT. HEALTH CLUB - DUSK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sunlight is dying when Sarah swings her moped to the curb in front of the 'GOOD LIFE SPA', a large, crowded health club.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 39 INT. HEALTH CLUB/AEROBICS STUDIO
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MUSIC BOOMS and masses of leotarded cellulite sway in close F.G. as CAMERA DOLLIES along a row of panting, stretching women.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In deep B.G. Sarah slips in through the door and waits against the wall while the human dynamo, GINGER VENTURA, leads the class energetically.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ginger, Sarah's roommate, is a party-stopper.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Red-haired, athletic, sensuous.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She's pretty enough when still, but stunning in motion.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And she's in motion.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ginger yells commands and cheerfully dives into contortions to the BEAT of a MOTOWN FAVORITE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MARCO, a handsome, well-defined guy wearing a tight STAFF T-shirt, strolls up for a drink at the water fountain next to Sarah.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MARCO
{DIALOGUE}: Hi.
{DIALOGUE}: I've seen you around.
{DIALOGUE}: You're cute.
{DIALOGUE}: Cute I remember.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: I'm Sarah.
{DIALOGUE}: Ginger's roommate.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MARCO
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah, right.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm Marco.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The dance tape ends.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GINGER
{DIALOGUE}: ...and three aaand four!
{DIALOGUE}: And that's it ladies!
{DIALOGUE}: Now, didn't that feel good?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The group collapses ensemble.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A chorus of groans.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GINGER
{DIALOGUE}: Let's think positive or next time I'll play the FM version.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ginger walks over to Sarah as the class disperses.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Marco is leaning on the wall next to Sarah, who is enjoying the attention.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: ...yeah, really?
{DIALOGUE}: Say some- thing in Italian.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Before Marco can reply, Ginger pulls the front of his gym shorts out and peers down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She shakes her head.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GINGER
{DIALOGUE}: You're wasting your time, kiddo.
{DIALOGUE}: Let's go.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She grabs Sarah by the arm and pulls her out the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah catches a glimpse of Marco's expression over her shoulder as the door closes.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 40 INT. HEALTH CLUB/STAIRS AND CORRIDOR
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PANAGLIDE WITH THE TWO GIRLS, as they descend to the first floor and enter a hallway Sarah is gasping with laughter.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{META_DATA}: (weakly)
{DIALOGUE}: I don't believe you did that.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ginger is adjusting her ever-present WALKMAN-TYPE CASSETTE PLAYER at her hip.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She slips on the earphones as they walk along.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah feigns outrage.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: I had him hooked.
{DIALOGUE}: He was just about to ask me out.
{DIALOGUE}: I could tell.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GINGER
{DIALOGUE}: That guy's a jerk.
{DIALOGUE}: I did you a favor.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: I'll do the same for you sometime.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah laughs and claps her friend on the back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They turn in at a door marked WEIGHT ROOM.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 41 INT. WEIGHT ROOM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SEVERAL ANGLES, on glistening arms, legs, torsos merging into bio-mechanical kinetic sculptures with the chrome-steel levers and tubes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The CRASH and SQUEAL of metal against metal.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In F.G., two Conan-esque arms thrust upward, glistening.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ginger's boyfriend, MATT McCALLISTER, the assistant manager of the club, strains out his last reps, bench-pressing enormous weight on the Nautilus machine.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Despite his imposing appearance, Matt is one of the warmest people you'd ever want to meet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His face is contorted, muscles knotted for the last push.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He heaves it up with a guttural cry.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lowering his weights with a CLANG, Matt lies panting, arms dangling at his side, eyes closed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A pair of female legs appear.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GINGER (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: What's this?
{DIALOGUE}: Sleep therapy?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Matt opens his eyes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GINGER
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: You think somebody's gonna do this for you?
{DIALOGUE}: Look at those shriveled bi's.
{DIALOGUE}: And you haven't worked lat's or ab's since Wednesday.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MATT
{META_DATA}: (smiling)
{DIALOGUE}: Hello, sweetheart.
{DIALOGUE}: Had a rough day?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GINGER
{META_DATA}: (softening)
{DIALOGUE}: Come here, wimp.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She leans down as he sits up and they meet in a kiss that's bad for the other guys' discipline.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah waits until they break the clinch to speak.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: Hi, Matt.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Matt look backwards over the bench, and replies, upside-down.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MATT
{META_DATA}: (grinning broadly)
{DIALOGUE}: Heeey!
{DIALOGUE}: It's my favorite Sarah.
{DIALOGUE}: Hi, babe.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ginger pulls the pin on Mat's weights and re-inserts it beneath the entire stack, the maximum weight.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GINGER
{DIALOGUE}: Alright, warm-ups are over.
{DIALOGUE}: Back to work, Bunky.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ginger readadjusts her headphones as the two girls walk away.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MATT
{DIALOGUE}: 'Bye beautiful.
{DIALOGUE}: You too, Ginger.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Two weightlifters nearby look at each other, than at Matt.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WEIGHTLIFTER
{DIALOGUE}: Bunky?
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 42 EXT. HEALTH CLUB/STREETS - DUSK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah lurches away from the curb on her moped, almost spilling Ginger who is attempting to ride double.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They swing out onto a main thoroughfare and careen through the bumper-to-bumper traffic.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah maneuvers deftly though overloaded and unstable.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ginger doesn't know whether to laugh of scream at the near-misses.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She does both.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 43 OMITTED
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 44 EXT. STREET/CONSTRUCTION SIGHT - DUSK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On a side street the girls pass an excavation site between high-rises.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They pass OUT OF FRAME as CAMERA HOLDS on the construction area and Ginger's shrieks fade.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In the F.G., under an overpass, Reese sits is a car watching the powerful machines moving earth.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's in a late-model non-descript GREY SEDAN, one of a row of cars gathering dirt beside the construction site.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Crab-armed back-hoes and massive caterpillars ROAR through a curtain of dust, under intense floodlights.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A power-shovel moves its great arm, lighting its own way with an arc-light.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 45 INT. GREY SEDAN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese sits motionless in the dark.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Waiting.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The clock in the dash ticks quietly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He flips on the radio.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A fatuous POP ROCK STATION.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese fishes a magazine off the dirty floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His over- coat is off, draped over the shotgun on the seat beside him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His bare arms are sinewy and scarred.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese flips the page of COSMOPOLITAN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He look at the glossy photos, the glossy women.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Fantasy women.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Svelte and seamless.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The ads fascinate him too: Caribbean vacations and blended whiskeys.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His head sags against the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He gazes dully at the tracks of a passing CATERPILLAR as they chew through the dirt.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The ROAD and CLATTER of treads intensifies as his eyes close.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 46 EXT. MELTED RUINS - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TIGHT ON A GLEAMING STEEL TREAD as it grinds through debris.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The debris is ferroconcrete, girders, and jackstraw heaps of HUMAN BONES, burned black.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There is the sound of EXPLOSIONS, distant, and an intermittent electronic WHINE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Incredibly bright searchlights play over the ground.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PANNING with the moving treads through twisted wreckage, F.G.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The screen WHITES OUT with a BLAST, very close.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As the debris clatters down, a helmetted head snaps up into FRAME, EXTREME F.G.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The visor of the HIGH-TECH HELMET is shattered, presumably by the explosion.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The wearer rips it off, revealing a younger Reese, minus his burn scar.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His face is bathed in sweat, lit by the glow from a CRT SCOPE-SIGHT on a strange-looking rifle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The sound of SCREAMS and HOARSE SHOUTS not far off, and a continuous low murmuring of RADIO CHATTER, grid coordinates, casualties, unit placements, medic requests.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese looks over his shoulder at his teammate, a GIRL of about sixteen, gaunt, dirty, heavily armed like himself.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DOLLYING as they start to belly crawl through the bones and wreckage.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese looks up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Through spires of a collapsed building a terrifying SPHINX-LIKE SHAPE moves against the sky...obscured by dust and blinding sweeps of its searchlights.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Though we see little, this is an H-K,Hunter-Killer mobile ground-unit.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese crawls, pacing the H-K, under and through, on elbows and knees, past mounds of charred skulls.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They pass the BODY OF A CHILD, a boy of about 10, center- punched with a smoking hole.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The boy clutches a rifle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: More bodies.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Some in rags, some in uniforms like theirs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WOMEN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OLD MEN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CHILDREN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They're all dirty and gaunt, scabrous.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And still bleeding.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese scrabbles past a dark rat-hole and there are human rats in it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Some of them are sobbing, or screaming.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Another EXPLOSION.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The GLARE lights the huddled few.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Human vermin with mud-caked weapons that haven't been invented yet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Soldiers in a nightmare war.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese and his teammate stop behind a blasted wall, having outflanked the massive H-K.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Its flashing blue lights flick across the walls, its searchlights sear through the debris.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WIDER, showing the H-K more clearly...a blast-scarred CHROME LEVIATHON, with hydraulic arms folded mantis-like against its 'torso', and huge underslung GUN TURRETS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese leaps up and straight-arms a satchel-charge into its path.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: One tread rolls over the explosive.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Guns and searchlights swivel.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The head turns ponderously.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese's partner rises, poised to throw hers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A POWER-BOLT catches her at the top of her arc, BLOWING HER INTO RED MIST.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese is knocked down by the concussion.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gets up, running, as the charges blow.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The H-K's tread carriers are RIPPED APART.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It lurches to a stop, burning.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The following SEQUENCE is extremely FORESHORTENED.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CUT FAST.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IMPRESSIONS ONLY.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Running.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Explosions light the ruins like flashbulbs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ENERGY WEAPONS criss-cross the night like tracers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LOW ANGLE, up past the burning H-K as its flying counter- part, an AERIAL H-K, arcs into view with a TURBOJET WHINE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese hauls two survivors of his unit into a PERSONNEL CARRIER, a CHEVY CAMARO with steel plate welded over it and the roof cut away to access the 50 CALIBER MACHINE GUN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's stripped and rusted and bullet-riddled, glassless.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The TIRES are OFF-ROAD and very gnarly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They're driving through the ruins, up and over and through.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese drives like a demon.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Under other circumstances it would be considered insane.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Here it is merely very good.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The machine gun CHATTERS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A BLACK SHAPE descends, a demon with searchlights.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A BOLT OF LIGHT.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese's car flips like a kicked beer can, rolling and crumpling.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's pinned in the wreck, bloody, screaming despite his training.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The only other survivor, an emaciated BOY of twelve, is pulling for all he's worth to drag Reese out before it burns.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 47 EXT. STREET/GREY SEDAN - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON A BOY, about twelve, clean and healthy, wearing a blue plastic DODGERS HELMET.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He reaches through the window of the sedan.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOY
{DIALOGUE}: Hey, mister...?
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 48 INT. GREY SEDAN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese's eyes open in a split-second, and suddenly there is a SHOTGUN MUZZLE AIMED RIGHT AT US.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese quivers with a curious spasm, similar to the tremors of his arrival, and blinks at the boy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The boy is white-faced, staring down the bore.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He backs away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We see that he is straddling a bicycle.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 49 EXT. GREY SEDAN - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The boy's SISTER, slightly younger and also on a bicycle, can't see the shotgun from where she's waiting.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SISTER
{META_DATA}: (taunting)
{DIALOGUE}: See, I told you he wasn't dead.
{DIALOGUE}: You owe me Baskin Robbins.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The boy rides past her list a shot.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BOY
{META_DATA}: (urgently)
{DIALOGUE}: Come on.
{DIALOGUE}: Just come on.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 50 INT. GREY SEDAN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese relaxes slowly, the voltage draining out of him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: INSERT - MACRO, Reese's finger on the trigger is white with pressure.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He slips the safety to the OFF position.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The gun can now be fired.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He sets it on the seat and reaches for the dangling ignition wires, starting the car.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 51 EXT. STREET/OVERPASS - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lit by streetlights, the car moves away with it lights off and vanishes in the shadows.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 52 OMITTED
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 53 INT. SARAH'S APARTMENT/BATHROOM/LIVING ROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah and Ginger are crammed into the tiny bathroom, becoming inextricably tangled in each other's cords as they blow-dry, curl hair, and apply make-up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ginger has her headphones inverted under her chin but in place, and is bouncing to music as she dries her hair.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She is wearing a short terry-cloth bathrobe that reveals the greater part of her legs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah is in a skirt and bra.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The phone rings and Sarah goes out into the living room to get it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{META_DATA}: (answering the phone)
{DIALOGUE}: Hello?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VOICE (V.O.)
{META_DATA}: (on phone, deep and breathy)
{DIALOGUE}: First I'm going to rip the buttons off your blouse, one by one...then run my tongue along your neck, down to your bare, gleaming breasts...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah cups her hand over the mouthpiece and calls out matter-of-factly:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: Ginger!
{DIALOGUE}: It's Matt.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She resumes listening.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MATT (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: ...and then slowly pull your jeans off inch by inch and lick your belly in circles, further and further down... then I'll pull off your panties with my teeth...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah is repressing laughter.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{META_DATA}: (crossly)
{DIALOGUE}: Who is this?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Silence.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then Matt realizes to his horror who he's been talking to.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MATT (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Oh my God!
{DIALOGUE}: Sarah!
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, shit.
{DIALOGUE}: Jesus, I'm sorry.
{DIALOGUE}: I thought you were...Can I talk to Ginger?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: Sure, Bunky.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Ginger approaches, Sarah hands her the receiver and goes into the bedroom.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GINGER
{DIALOGUE}: Hello?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MATT (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: First I'm gonna rip the buttons off your blouse...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 54 BEDROOM
