{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: You think the beige?
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 56 EXT. VENICE STREET - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An unmarked car with a clamp-on light and siren blaring screeches to the curb behind two marked black-and-whites in front of a funky Venice apartment building.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A small crowd is gathered around the front steps.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LIEUTENANT ED VUKOVICH, Homicide Division, gets out of the car and strides through the crowd.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's fiftyish, short, but square and solid, a human bulldog gone a little to paunch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He chews Juicy Fruit gum like a maniac: a chain-chewer.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's homely as an old boot.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And he's not a smart cop, he's a wise one; rarer still.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The onlookers, gathered patiently for their ten second glimpse of something under a sheet, separate for him to pass.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 57 INT. VENICE APARTMENT BUILDING/STAIRWELL/APARTMENT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CAMERA PANAGLIDES AHEAD OF VUKOVICH, as he climbs the switch- back staircase two steps at a time.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He passes TWO UNIFORMED COPS at the doorway of a second-floor apartment, and enters to find a quiet flurry of activity.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Several DETECTIVES and a PHOTOGRAPHER prowl around, taking evidence, taking pictures.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In the center of the living room floor is the body of a young woman, crumpled face down in a small lake of blood.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Two bags of groceries lie split open on the floor in front of her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vukovich glances up as he is joined by DETECTIVE SGT. TRAXLER.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Traxler is black, lean and very jaded.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VUKOVICH
{DIALOGUE}: Give me the short version.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TRAXLER
{DIALOGUE}: Six shots at less than ten feet.
{DIALOGUE}: Weapon was a large caliber--
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vukovich is looking at the body.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VUKOVICH
{DIALOGUE}: No shit.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Traxler turns to a passing DETECTIVE.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TRAXLER
{DIALOGUE}: Come on.
{DIALOGUE}: man.
{DIALOGUE}: Don't track it all over.
{DIALOGUE}: It's un- professional.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turn back to Vukovich, gesturing at the body.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TRAXLER
