{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 60 INT. PARKING GARAGE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah is a small figure in the shadowed echoing garage of her building.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CONVERGING DOLLY, PACING HER, as she passes the stalls with their inky shadows.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The light near her moped is out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She fumbles in the dark to unlock the chain.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She looks up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Did she hear something...masked by the rattle of the chain?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: POV - SARAH, there is no movement for the length of the garage.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ON SARAH - C.U., inexplicably nervous.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She stows the chain and starts the bike.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It whines reassuringly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah jumps on and whirs out of the garage.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 61 INT. CAR/NEARBY - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah is visible through the windshield as she pulls onto the street.
