{DIALOGUE}: On a lighter note, these was cause for celebration at the L.A. Zoo today, as...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah leaves her half-finished pizza and beer, getting up in a daze.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Followed by puzzles glances, she makes her way through the crowd.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 68 INT. PIZZA PARLOR HALLWAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In the crowded hallway by the restrooms, Sarah goes to the single payphone and seizes the directory.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She flips rapidly through it, then stops, looking down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She sees that her name is next on the list.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The book slips out of her fingers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah turns and scans the crowd.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She's getting looks, covert and otherwise, like any unaccom- panied girl on a Friday night.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But is that all they mean?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah back into the women's restroom.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 69 INT. RESTROOM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah stumbles numbly to the sink.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She splashes her face with cold water.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In the mirror her terrified reflection looks back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Why me?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She hears a loud clatter and spins around.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's just a drunken woman fumbling with a toilet stall door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah edges back out into the corridor.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 70 INT. HALLWAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah walks stiffly to the pay phone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's OUT OF ORDER.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 71 EXT. STREET/SIDEWALK - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah exits the pizza place into the sparse crowd on the sidewalk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As she passes a figure leaning against the wall just outside, the man turns his head to watch her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is Reese, his gaze impassive.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Streetlight catches the burn scar on his cheek.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is motionless, sinister in his long coat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah shudders.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She walks on.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: POV - SARAH, ON CROWD, moving toward and through approaching groups of pedestrians.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They seem to be glancing at her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Was it always like that and she just never noticed?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: C.U. - SARAH as she look over her shoulder.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: POV - SARAH, ON PIZZA PARLOR DOORWAY.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese is gone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She resists the urge to run.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On the opposite side of the street an LAPD cruiser glides slowly by.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah is about to call out but a bus blocks her view and when it had passed, the car is turning away down a side street.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She passes a large window with STOKER'S written on it, and ducks quickly through the door.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 72 INT. STOKER'S - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE THROUGH WINDOW, SARAH F.G., as Reese approaches.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her knuckles clench white as he reaches the entrance and walks by, unhurriedly, without a glance inside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She turns and scan the gloomy interior, which reveals itself to be less than savory.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pool tables and upper-middle lowlife in submarine depths of smoky haze.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah draws stares, menacing in their own right, as she weaves between the pool tables to the back of the bar.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: her hands are trembling as she drops a dime in the pay phone and dials.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VOICE (V.O./RECORDED)
{DIALOGUE}: You have reached the Los Angeles Police Department Emergency Number.
{DIALOGUE}: All lines are busy.
{DIALOGUE}: If you need a police car sent out to you, please stay on the line...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah holds the receiver pressed to her ear, glancing around, fear feeding on frustration.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 73 EXT. SARAH'S APARTMENT BUILDING - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An LAPD black-and-white sits at the curb in front of Sarah's building with two cops inside, drinking coffee.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Through the open window we hear the dispatcher's voice on the radio.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DISPATCHER (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: ...two eleven in progress at Seven-Eleven market, Third and Tamarac.
{DIALOGUE}: One suspect believed to be armed...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The car pulls out with lights and siren on.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A moment later, Terminator rounds the corner of the building and climbs the stairs to the entryway.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He surveys the bank of call buttons, then turns to consider the barred security gate.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 74 INT. SARAH'S APARTMENT - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PANAGLIDE WITH GINGER as she ties her terry-cloth robe and, leaving Matt in a dead sleep, pads through the dark apartment.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Down the hall, past the phone with Traxler's message.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Through the dark living room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She has her Walkman in the pocket of her robe and bops to herself in the silent gloom as she enters the kitchen.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: When she opens the refrigerator to remove snack fixings, the light briefly illuminates the kitchen and in that moment, SOMETHING MOVES in the F.G.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TIGHT ON GINGER, MOVING WITH HER as she backs toward the counter with her arms full of snack stuff.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A SUDDEN CRASH.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A flurry of motion behind her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She spins, dropping half her load.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ginger fumbles for the lightswitch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Revealing Pugsley, sitting there blinking innocently among overturned spice bottles on the counter-top.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GINGER
{DIALOGUE}: Shoo.
{DIALOGUE}: Go on.
{DIALOGUE}: I'll make a belt out of you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pugsley disappears into a large fern by the window and Ginger sets about her task, slathering crunchy peanut butter on stalks of celery.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 75 INT. BEDROOM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MEDIUM ON MATT, as rustling curtains play patterns of street- light over his sleeping face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The sound of a faint breeze.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In the B.G. is the balcony, empty.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The sliding door is open.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TIGHT ON MATT, as his eyes open at the sound of a quiet, repeated CLICKING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: UP ANGLE - PAST MATT, as the five-inch blade of an industrial razor-knife reaches full extension in Terminator's hand, right above him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It slashes viciously downward.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Matt rolls and the pillow is SLIT OPEN where his throat had been.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MATT
{DIALOGUE}: Whoah!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator catches him by the hair and slashed down again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Matt grabs the wrist in both hands.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The enormous muscles of his arms, which seem capable of bench pressing a Chrysler, strain and knot against the pressure of the killer's single arm... And still the blade moves closer to his throat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With a final heave Matt deflects the down-pressure sideways and the blade snaps with a CLINK against the headboard.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HANDHELD WITH MATT as he rolls off the bed, spins and slams his fists together into Terminator's temple.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He picks up a brass deco lamp and brings it down with piledriver force.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Unperturbed, Terminator knocks the lamp away and hurls Matt over the bed.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 76 EXT. BALCONY - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Matt crashes through the glass doors and slams against the balcony railing.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 77 INT. KITCHEN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Oblivious to the noise, Ginger croons in rock-and-roll ecstasy, singing to a celery stalk as if it were a micro- phone.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 78 EXT./INT. BALCONY AND BEDROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Matt heaves himself up, powerful body gleaming with sweat and hurls himself upon the intruder.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The titans CRASH INTO A DRESSER, reducing it to kindling.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then into the closet door, EXPLODING THE FULL-LENGTH MIRROR.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator places one hand on either side of Matt's barrel chest.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SINKS HIS FINGERS INTO THE FLESH.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An inhuman grip.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Matt is raised off the floor, contorted with agony, above the other's head.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 79 INT. HALLWAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DOLLY PRECEDING GINGER as she returns from the kitchen with a plate full of celery stalks and a glass of milk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CAMERA passes the closed bedroom door and STOPS, as Ginger pauses to set the plate on top of the glass, freeing one hand to open the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: AN EXPLOSION OF SPLINTERS in close F.G. as a shape smashes through the door right in front of her...Matt's body propelled halfway through the door by enormous force.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ginger shrieks and leaps back, flinging milk and all into the air.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The door begins to open the pressure of Matt's body creates resistance.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ginger SCREAMS and back away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The door is wrenched open and Terminator steps through with the massive .45 drawn.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HANDHELD WITH GINGER, the walls blur by as she runs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TIGHT ON TERMINATOR as the pistol RISES INTO FRAME, aligning with his eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BOOM!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LOW FAST DOLLY WITH GINGER as the bullet punches into her shoulder, pitching her on her face outside the bathroom door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LOW WIDE ANGLE as she crawls forward, gasping, drowning.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The implacable figure looms behind her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her expression is agony and reeling, nauseating terror.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And incomprehension: Why am I suddenly dying?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her eyes roll, showing the whites, like a horse tethered in a burning stable.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 80 INT. BATHROOM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ginger scrabbles pathetically for a grip on the tile floor as she pulls herself into the bathroom.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She clutches the rim of the toilet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LOW ANGLE PAST HER, ON TERMINATOR, as he stands behind her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PAN UP, off her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He takes aim.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And empties the clip.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He calmly reloads.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 81 INT. HALLWAY/BEDROOM
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE ON PHONE MACHINE, as the telephone rings loudly in the ensuing silence.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator spins, drawing an instantaneous bead on the source of the sound, but doesn't fire.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GINGER'S VOICE
{META_DATA}: (recorded)
{DIALOGUE}: Hi there.
{META_DATA}: (pause)
{DIALOGUE}: Ha ha ha, fooled you.
{DIALOGUE}: You're talking to a machine...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: C.U. - TERMINATOR, motionless, listening.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GINGER'S VOICE
{META_DATA}: (recorded, continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: ...but don't be shy, it's okay.
{DIALOGUE}: Machines need love too...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator turns abruptly back to Ginger's body.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns it over, assuring himself that she is dead.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GINGER'S VOICE
{META_DATA}: (continuing, recorded)
{DIALOGUE}: ...so talk to it and Ginger, that's me, or Sarah will get back to you.
{DIALOGUE}: Wait for the beep.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There is a loud tone and the incoming call is heard.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH'S VOICE
{META_DATA}: (on machine)
{DIALOGUE}: Ginger, this is Sarah...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator's head snaps back and he freezes, listening.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He rises slowly as Sarah's voice continues.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TIGHT ON HIS UNBLINKING EYES.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH'S VOICE
{META_DATA}: (on machine, contin- uing)
{DIALOGUE}: ...I'm in this sleazy bar called Stoker's on Pico but I'm too scared to leave.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm really scared, kiddo...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 82 INT. STOKER'S BAR - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah cups the telephone's mouthpiece with her hand and glances around frequently.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{META_DATA}: (continuing, into phone)
{DIALOGUE}: ...I think somebody's after me and I sure hope you play this soon 'cause I need you and Matt to come pick me up.
{DIALOGUE}: The police keep transferring me around, but I'm going to try them again.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 83 INT. SARAH'S APARTMENT/BEDROOM - NIGHT
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{META_DATA}: (continuing, B.G.)
{DIALOGUE}: The number here is 468-9175.
{DIALOGUE}: Call me, kiddo.
{DIALOGUE}: I need you.
{DIALOGUE}: It's Stoker's on Pico.
{DIALOGUE}: Bye.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator is rapidly and methodically rifling the contents of Sarah's small desk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SIREN'S WAIL, approaching.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He picks up a small card.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: E.C.U. - CARD.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is Sarah's college I.D. card, complete with color photo of her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MACRO ON PICTURE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: E.C.U. - TERMINATOR'S EYES as he tosses the card down, after a fraction of a second's scan.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Picks up something else.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TIGHT ON SARAH'S ADDRESS BOOK, Terminator pockets this and slips out the balcony door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Climbing over the railing, he is gone.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 84 INT. STOKER'S BAR - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah is huddled, back to the wall, beside the phone.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{META_DATA}: (on phone, upset)
{DIALOGUE}: ...look, Lieutenant...uh, Vukovich, don't put me on hold and don't transfer me to another department...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 85 INT. VUKOVICH'S OFFICE - NIGHT
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VUKOVICH
{META_DATA}: (on phone)
{DIALOGUE}: I won't.
{DIALOGUE}: Now just relax.
{DIALOGUE}: Where are you?
{META_DATA}: (pause)
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah, I know it...on Pico.
{DIALOGUE}: Are you alright?
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 86 INT. STOKER'S BAT - NIGHT
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{META_DATA}: (on phone)
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, but I don't want to leave.
{DIALOGUE}: I think this guy's following me.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 87 INT. VUKOVICH'S OFFICE - NIGHT
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VUKOVICH
{META_DATA}: (on phone)
{DIALOGUE}: Alright, Ms. Connor.
{DIALOGUE}: Listen carefully.
{DIALOGUE}: You're in a public place, you'll be safe 'til we get there.
{DIALOGUE}: Stay visible.
{DIALOGUE}: Don't go outside or in the restroom.
{DIALOGUE}: I'll be there in a few minutes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He hangs up and grabs his coat, motioning to Traxler.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VUKOVICH
{DIALOGUE}: Let's roll.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 88 INT. STOKER'S BAR - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah takes a seat at a booth near the bar, and picks up a dog-eared menu, but can't concentrate on it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She looks at her watch and glances around.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 89 EXT. STREET - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The yellow Maverick hurtles along an empty street.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSER ANGLE as streetlight glare slashes across Terminator's face in flaring pulses.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 90 INT. PLAIN CAR - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vukovich draws his Colt Python .357 Magnum and check the load.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Traxler is driving.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VUKOVICH
{DIALOGUE}: Let's see how this guy likes playing hard-ball.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 91 INT. STOKER'S BAR - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The waitress set a cup of coffee in front of Sarah.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WAITRESS
{DIALOGUE}: Anything else?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah shakes her head "No" and contemplates her trembling hands.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She half-turns, catching a glimpse of herself in the mirror behind the bar.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TIGHT ON SARAH, reflected in the mirror.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In the F.G. a man at the bar looks up from his beer, straight into her eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is Reese.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He gazes at her coolly for a moment, then glances away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: C.U. - SARAH, feeling trapped, frantic.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON FRONT DOOR as it opens and a figure stands silhou- etted briefly against a streetlight.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese turns, his eyes flickering to the mirror, the figure.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: C.U. - REESE as he mechanically raises his beer.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His knuckles are white.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He slowly undoes the top button of his overcoat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There is a glint of metal in the shadows within.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese turns slowly on his barstool as the figure brushes past him, out-of-focus F.G. Sarah looks up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: E.C.U. - REESE'S HAND sliding slowly along polished steel, a caress.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His finger slips through the triggerguard of the riot gun.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MEDIUM ON SARAH, as the man stops in front of her in close F.G.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He sits slowly in the booth opposite her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The angle is OVER HIS SHOULDER.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{META_DATA}: (uncertainly)
{DIALOGUE}: Lieutenant Vukovich?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: REVERSE ANGLE - It is not Lt. Vukovich.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator sits motionless for a BEAT.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Blue eyes so pure and deep.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The eyes of a saint, perhaps.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The .45 is out and cocked and AIMED DIRECTLY AT CAMERA, almost in one motion.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The bore seems enormous.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BACK ON SARAH, over the gun barrel, her eyes go wide.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We hold a BEAT, like a frozen slice of nightmare.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MEDIUM ON REESE as he whips the riot-gun to a hip-firing posi- tion, his overcoat falling back with a snap.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HE FIRES.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ON TERMINATOR, as the shotgun blast hits his arm and he FIRES, simultaneously.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah screams as the .45 round blows stuffing out of the booth seat inches from her face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her hair is singed by burning gunpowder.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An involuntary cry is punched out of her by the double concussions.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese is stroking up another shell as Terminator half-rises from booth.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OVER REESE'S SHOULDER, as he fires, cocks the slide, fires again, advancing on Sarah's booth.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator is blown backward over the center divider, crashing through the glasses and pitchers of beer on the table opposite, and onto the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah is screaming, scrunched down in the booth.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator is lying on his back at the feet of a table- full of drunk patrons.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He has two rifled 12 gauge slugs in his chest and one in the arm.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The bar customers are frozen in the weird tableau, cowering, gaping.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah stops screaming.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese stand motionless, gun aimed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In the sudden silence, the sound of him cocking the shotgun is abnormally loud.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ON TERMINATOR, very still.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then he smoothly rolls to a crouch and slips the UZI machine pistol from beneath his overcoat, where it has been hang- ing on a shoulder strap.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He doesn't seem too impaired as he swings around to fire.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese rolls like a cat and comes up firing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A burst from the UZI rakes the bar where he stood.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An orgy of shattering glass.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Total pandemonium.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SEVERAL ANGLES as patrons of the bar run, scream or dive for cover, depending upon their level of intelligence.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese slides through the glass to Sarah's booth and seizes her wrists.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ON TERMINATOR, kneeling amid the chaos, raising the UZI one-handed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese tugs viciously on Sarah's arm and she sprawls across the booth seat a moment before the divider and seat cushion erupt with hits from the UZI.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON A RUNNING PATRON as a burst of 9mm fire catches him in the chest.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pitches into Sarah's booth, pinning her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese fires, ducks, fires again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tables crash over.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A window is blown out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A table candle rolls into a pool of high-proof alcohol behind the bar.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It ignites with a WHOOSH.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese feed two shells into the riot-gun.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TIGHT ON TERMINATOR, an island of slow, precise movement amid the confusion.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He drops a spent clip.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reaches for another with his bloody hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MOVING WITH REESE as he vaults the row of booths and starts firing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: At point blank range he unloads the shotgun into Terminator's belly.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 92 INT./EXT. STOKER'S/STREET - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator crashes backwards through two tables and a plate glass window into the street.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 93 INT. STOKER'S BAR - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The roaring fire behind the bar is spreading very quickly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The air is thick with smoke.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese tosses the UZI, for which he has no ammo, into the fire.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He hauls the dead man off Sarah and reaches for her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TIGHT ON SARAH, shrinking away from Reese, hysterical.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: When he grabs her wrist she struggles, eyes wide.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: C.U. - REESE, very intense.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{DIALOGUE}: Come with me if you want to live.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She looks where he is pointing.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 94 EXT. STOKER'S BAR/STREET - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator is rising unsteadily to his feet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Shattered glass rains from him, except where it sticks to his blood- drenched shirt and coat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: C.U. - TERMINATOR, as he slowly look up, his blue eyes riveting STRAIGHT INTO THE CAMERA.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 95 INT. STOKER'S BAR - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: C.U. - SARAH, feeling a lightning blot of terror greater than she could ever imagine as the cold gaze fixes on her.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{META_DATA}: (awed whisper)
{DIALOGUE}: Oh my God...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 96 INT./EXT. STOKER'S BAR - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PANAGLIDE PRECEDING TERMINATOR as he clambers back through the window and starts through the burning bar.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 97 INT. STOKER'S BAR - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PANAGLIDE MOVING IN ON REESE AND SARAH as he runs, drag- ging her with him, toward the back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: REVERSE ON TERMINATOR, DOLLYING as he crashed through the wreckage in the swirling smoke, hurling burning tables out of his way.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 98 INT. KITCHEN/HALLWAY/EXIT CORRIDOR
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PANAGLIDE FOLLOWING REESE AND SARAH, running headlong through the cluttered kitchen, then down a narrow back hallway.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah stumbles and Reese brutally pulls her to her feet without slowing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He hits a closed door, which crashes open.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hauls Sarah through, into another corridor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Slams and blot-latches it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An instant later an impact from the far side tears the latch-screws half out of the wall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They run on.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 99 INT. HALLWAY - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator takes a step back from the closed door and slams into it again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It starts to give way.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: behind him the flames engulf a CAN OF CLEANING SOLVENT.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 100 INT./EXT. EXIT CORRIDOR/ALLEY - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese and Sarah pelt down the narrow corridor, fling open the outside door and spin out into the alley.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TIGHT ON DOOR at far end.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It splinters open and Terminator sprints down the corridor.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 101 INT. HALLWAY - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The cleaning solvent EXPLODES.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 102 INT. EXIT CORRIDOR - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DOLLYING AHEAD OF TERMINATOR, very fast, as he runs full- throttle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Behind him a fireball of superheated gas hurtles down the narrow hallway.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He clears the outer door an instant before the tongue of flame roars out into the alley.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 103 EXT. STREET IN FRONT OF STOKER'S - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vukovich's plain car arrives, slewing to a stop in the glass-littered street in front of the blazing building.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He leaps out, Traxler right in behind him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VUKOVICH
{META_DATA}: (shouting)
{DIALOGUE}: What the fuck is going on?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TWO LAPD UNITS arrive behind them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He motions to the nearest one.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VUKOVICH
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: Cover the alley in back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He heads for the inferno at a run.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 104 EXT. ALLEY BEHIND STOKER'S - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DOLLYING WITH REESE AND SARAH as they run through the dark alley.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah stumbles over trashcans.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese pulls her along mercilessly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WHIP-PANNING as they clear a corner.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The B.G. is a blur.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The night-maze is a blur in all of these shots.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No static angles.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Relentless forward motion.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 105/FX EXT. ALLEY - NIGHT 105/FX
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Behind them Terminator is moving with inhuman speed, bounding like a panther, leaping trash cans and other obstacles.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TRACKING C.U. - TERMINATOR, catching the faintest glimpse of a red glow in the pupils of his eyes as he passes through total shadow.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 106/FX EXT. ALLEY/POV - TERMINATOR (HANDHELD) - NIGHT 106/FX
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We know this is Terminator's POV because Sarah and Reese are just ahead of us.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But the image is bizarre, alien.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bright and hyper-real.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There is a hint of digitization, and the fleeing figures ahead are more luminous than the background, suggesting infra-red.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The margins of the FRAME are crammed with columns of CRT- type characters: columns of numbers and acronyms.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The data changes more rapidly than any human eye could follow.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There is no doubt that we are seeing as a machine would see.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The sound effects are bright and clear, as if they are digitized and enhanced as well.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 107 EXT. ADJOINING ALLEY - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese and Sarah turn a corner by caroming off the wall without slowing and pelt down a narrower alley.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: This one is lined with a row of parked cars and connects to the street.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There is little room to run.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese is reloading on the run, dropping shells.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Behind them Terminator enters the alley, gaining.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LOW ANGLE, FAST PANAGLIDE ahead of the fleeing pair.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As they breast the last car Reese shoves Sarah hard, pitching her on her face to the pavement.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He flings open the car door...a shield.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Drops to the ground.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Fires into the gas tank of a car further back in the row just before Terminator reaches it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The car EXPLODES, filling the alley with fire.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An inferno funneled between the enclosing walls.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON REESE AND SARAH behind the car door as flames roar over the hood.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ON TERMINATOR, as he slides to a stop, cut off by the wall of flame.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese doesn't waste any time stuffing Sarah into the car.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Climbing in after and over her he twists two wires together and we recognize it as his stolen GREY SEDAN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The engine catches.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A SILHOUETTE rockets out of the flames.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator, leaping from the roof of the blazing car ahead, impacts on the hood of Reese's car.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His hair and coat are burning.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 108 INT./EXT. GREY SEDAN/ALLEY - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese jams reverse and nail the throttle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The car backs down the alley.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator draws back his fist.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Punches into the windshield.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Inside, Sarah is sprayed with glass as the killer's fist shoots through.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The lacerated fingers grope for her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WIDE as the car shoots backwards out of the alley onto the street, narrowly missing an arriving LAPD CRUISER.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah plasters herself tightly into the seat as the fingers grasp her blouse and pull.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese cranks the wheel hard.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 109 EXT. STREET - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The sedan skids, slewing sideways into a parked car.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator rolls down off onto the pavement.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese's car shoots forward.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PANNING WITH SEDAN as it roars past Vukovich, the gathering minions of the burning building, an arriving fire truck...shoots through a red light and continues to accel- erate.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator gets to a kneeling position, then slowly stands.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pats out his smoldering clothing as he watches his quarry escape.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 110 EXT. STREET - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ON VUKOVICH as he runs to his car, exhorting the nearby LAPD guys to give pursuit, while Traxler grabs the radio.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VUKOVICH
{META_DATA}: (shouting)
{DIALOGUE}: Go!
{DIALOGUE}: Go!
{DIALOGUE}: He's got her.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TRAXLER
{META_DATA}: (overlapping)
{DIALOGUE}: Suspect westbound on Olympic.
{DIALOGUE}: Grey sedan.
{DIALOGUE}: Has hostage, repeat...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 111 EXT. STREET - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LOW WIDE ANGLE on the empty street, which is narrow and tightly lines with parked cars.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The ROAR of an engine builds.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The sedan, like a night-demon, hurtles out of the shadows with its lights off, doing ninety plus.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 112 INT. GREY SEDAN - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah is in a daze.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Paralyzed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Face bloodless.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She is shivering silently, uncontrollably.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her eyes are wide, and it seems likely that she doesn't quite comprehend the roaring blur outside her window.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{META_DATA}: (calmly)
{DIALOGUE}: Hold on.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 113 EXT. CITY STREETS - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WIDE ANGLE, CLOSE TO SEDAN, and following it as it hurtles around a corner in an expertly controlled slide.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then a high speed sprint down the cross-street.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese squirrels the vehicle between a slow-moving car ahead and oncoming traffic.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A dive into another dark side street.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 114 INT. GRAY SEDAN - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese drives with total, nerveless absorption.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His eyes flick to the mirror, to the road, over his shoulder, back ...and the world spins outside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With occasional glances to Sarah, he speaks to her in a clipped, military voice.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{DIALOGUE}: Are you injured?
{DIALOGUE}: Are you shot?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No response.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He reaches over and runs his hands over her arms, legs, chest.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah flinches.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She feels the BLIND PANIC BOILING UP WITHIN HER.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She pushes his hand away and opens the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese slams her back in the seat and slaps her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hard.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: Do exactly what I say.
{DIALOGUE}: Exactly.
{DIALOGUE}: Don't move un- less I say.
{DIALOGUE}: Don't make a sound unless I say.
{DIALOGUE}: Do you understand?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As he speaks he is locking the door and fastening Sarah's seatbelt over her, cinching it very tightly, like you would for a child.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She doesn't answer.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{META_DATA}: (continuing/ shouting)
{DIALOGUE}: Do you understand?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{META_DATA}: (a whisper)
{DIALOGUE}: Yes.
{DIALOGUE}: Don't hurt me.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{DIALOGUE}: I'm here to help you.
{DIALOGUE}: Reese, Sergeant/Tech-Com, DN38416...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah stares numbly at his outstretched hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With zero strength she automatically returns his handshake.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: Assigned to protect you.
{DIALOGUE}: You've been targetted for termination.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 115 EXT. SIDE STREET/ALLEY - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The walls of a narrow alley, inky black, frame a police cruiser parked on the street beyond.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Firelight from the back of Stoker's lights the street garishly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A young cop stands beside the car talking via radio with the mike cord pulled through the side window.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He speaks with a distinctive twang--a displaced southerner.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COP
{DIALOGUE}: ...I don't know, it looks like it might spread to this furniture warehouse across the alley, the paint on the wall's starting to blister up...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The sweeping headlights of a turning car momentarily illuminate the face of Terminator, motionless in the dark right in front of us.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Eyes open.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Listening.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: COP
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: Better get another truck round to this side.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator's silhouette emerges from the blackness and strides purposefully toward the cop, CAMERA following.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The officer whirls and reaches for his gun but Terminator flings him brutally into the side of the car, steps over him and opens the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Before getting in he notes the unit number on the roof: 143.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then he slides behind the wheel, slips the squad car into gear, and pulls out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CAMERA PRECEDING CAR, HIDE WIDE ANGLE, as it accelerates rapidly, until the lines across the street are flashing under it in a staccato rhythm.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 116 INT. GREY SEDAN - NIGHT
