{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They come to a red light and Reese stops.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{META_DATA}: (patronizingly)
{DIALOGUE}: Right...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Like a shot she unlatches the seatbelt, pulls the door lock and has the door half open before Reese can react.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He catches her arm and hauls her struggling back into the car.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah sinks her teeth into his hand with all her strength.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His grip doesn't slacken.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Slowly, without releasing her, he reaches across with his other hand and shuts the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His face shows no reaction.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah draws back and stares at the blood running down his arm from the bite, that at his grim, scarred face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The light turns green and Reese drives on.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah tastes blood and wipes her mouth.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{META_DATA}: (coldly)
{DIALOGUE}: Cyborgs don't feel pain.
{DIALOGUE}: I do.
