{DIALOGUE}: Patrol machines.
{DIALOGUE}: Build in automated factories.
{DIALOGUE}: Most of us were rounded up, put in camps...for orderly disposal.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pushes up the sleeve of his jacket and shows her a ten digit number etches on the skin of his forearm.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beneath the numbers is a pattern of lines like the auto- matic-pricing marks on product packages.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: Burned in by laser scan.
{META_DATA}: (pause)
{DIALOGUE}: Some of us were kept alive... to work.
{DIALOGUE}: Loading bodies.
{DIALOGUE}: The disposal units ran night and day.
{DIALOGUE}: We were that close to going out forever...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The helicopter moves overhead.
