{DIALOGUE}: You're a doctor?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SILBERMAN
{DIALOGUE}: A criminal psychologist.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: Is Reese crazy?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SILBERMAN
{DIALOGUE}: That's what we're going to find out.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 152 INT. HOTEL ROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The room costs five dollars a night and that's steep, but the FIRE ESCAPE outside the window adds an element of strategic value.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A silhouette slips in through the window and click on the single BARE LIGHT BULB.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's Terminator, and he's a mess.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A bloody scarecrow with bullet wounds in stomach, chest, shoulder and right wrist.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MEDIUM ON TERMINATOR as he sits at a ratty folding table under the light.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His eyebrows are singed off.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hair a charred stubble.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Left eyes glistening with imbedded glass shards.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Before him on the table is an array of SMALL TOOLS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He removes the charred remains of his jacket and props.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: one elbow on the table.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE PAST HIS NON-FUNCTIONAL RIGHT ARM, F.G., as he exam- ines it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He picks up an X-ACTO KNIFE and cuts deeply into the skin of his forearm.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His expression is one of mild concentration.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: E.C.U. - FOREARM, as he pulls back a large flap of skin to reveal a complex trunk of SHEATHED CABLES AND HYDRAULICS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They slide as he moves his fingers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: RESUME MEDIUM, as Terminator uses a rag to wipe away the blood.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With small screwdrivers he begins to patiently dis- assemble the damaged mechanism around the 12-guage hit.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 153 INT. DIVISION HQ/INTERROGATION ROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The room is small, furnished with only a table and two chairs.
