{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 158 INT. HOTEL ROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: E.C.U. - TERMINATOR, in profile, showing his lacerated eye.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is close to a mirror, practically touching it, staring intently.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MACRO - X-ACTO KNIFE lying on the dresser.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator's fingers lift it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CAMERA TILTS TO FOLLOW as it rises to his face, holds TIGHT ON left eye.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With a smooth motion the knife point enters the eyeball and cuts away the ruins sclera and cornea, as well as part of the damaged eyelids.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He wipes with a rag to clear the electronic eye's vision.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Revealing the faintly glowing lens mechanism, suspended in a chrome socket by tiny servos.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The eye whirs quietly as it tracks.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SEQUENCE OF SHOTS, showing various repairs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator's right hand, its wrist SUTURED crudely, holds a needle and sewing thread and starts to work on abdominal wound out of frame below.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He slips a glove over the damaged hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A motoring cap over the blistered scalp.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A fresh shirt to hide his body wounds.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: This is followed by a new overcoat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: C.U. - TERMINATOR, contemplating his reflection in the mirror.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With the hat pulled down, the collar pulled up, and favoring his right profile he looks unhurt...though a bit gaunt and pale.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A turn of his head brings the balefully glowing left eye in its metal socket into view.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He slips on a pair of tight, wrap-around sunglasses.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FULL SHOT as he goes to the bed and flips up the stained mattress.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He picks up the Remington 12 gauge, the AR-180 and the .38 off the springs and leaves by the fire escape.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
