{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE PAST DESK SERGEANT, F.G. - ON FRONT DOORS, the officer is absorbed in paperwork, not watching as a pair of lights get BRIGHTER outside the doors.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: RAPIDLY.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He glances up at the last second as the glare falls fully on him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CRASH!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Several cops and late night loiterers scatter as a car smashes into the foyer.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It blasts through the sergeant's booth, crushing him in the wreckage.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 161 INT. DIVISION HQ/VUKOVICH'S OFFICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah, lying on the couch, jerks awake as the crash REVERBERATES through the building.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She sits up, bleary- eyes.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 162 INT. DIVISION HQ/CORRIDOR
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Through the hole in the splintered wall we see Terminator leap out of the car.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He vaults the hood and smashes through the debris of the wall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Leaps to the corridor floor in a shower of plaster fragments.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He brandishes the AR-180 like a pistol in one hand, the .38 in the other.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The shotgun dangles at his side on a shoulder sling.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LOW ANGLE DOLLY, preceding him as he starts down the corridor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON LOUNGE DOORWAY as TWO COPS run into the hall, one carrying a cup of coffee.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator fires a burst from the assault rifle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON COPS - They are flung backward in a spray of coffee and plaster.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 163 INT. DIVISION HQ/VUKOVICH'S OFFICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah is alert now with growing alarm.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The sound of GUNFIRE is faint...but unmistakable.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her expression shows the dawning certainty of what is happening.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 164 INT. DIVISION HQ/CORRIDOR
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator steps over the bodies of the two cops without breaking stride.
