{DIALOGUE}: Whoah.
{DIALOGUE}: I hear that.
{META_DATA}: (pause)
{DIALOGUE}: Listen, I had a rough night.
{DIALOGUE}: I gotta stop and bag some Z's.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They pull off the highway toward a gas station/rest area.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 190 EXT. SERVICE STATION - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The gas station is like an oasis of clutter in a rolling stretch of meadows and woods.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It consists of a bunker- like building with restrooms and a flanking PICNIC AREA, beyond which are WOODS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: People sit under the trees, enjoying the beautiful day while children tear around after the forced inactivity of a long trip.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The three of them get out on unsteady legs.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DRIVER
{DIALOGUE}: You can still ride if you wanna hang out for a couple hours.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: Thanks.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{DIALOGUE}: Bag some Z's?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: Let's get cleaned up, Kyle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She heads for the WOMEN'S RESTROOM and Kyle follows her inside.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{META_DATA}: (pushing him out)
{DIALOGUE}: Yours is over there.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Instead of following her directions to the Men's Room, Kyle wanders toward the drinking fountain.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A bunch of kids are running around and throwing water at each other with paper cups.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese shambles through them like a zombie.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stands among the children, an alien in this land without fear.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He watches people at picnic tables laughing and listening to portable music.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kids squeal.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dogs bark.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LITTLE GIRL (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Can you get my balloon?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DOWN ANGLE on an achingly beautiful LITTLE GIRL of about four.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She points above his head.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese looks up to see a helium-filled mylar balloon stuck in the foliage of a tree just above him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pulls it down by the string and holds it, turning it over dully.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He crouches down to her eye-level.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She smiles.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{DIALOGUE}: Aren't you afraid to be out in the open like this?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LITTLE GIRL
{DIALOGUE}: Huh?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese whirls reflexively at a SCREAM behind him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The mylar balloon bursts in his tense hands.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A teenage girl is being doused with water by the boys with plastic jugs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The little girl looks at the broken balloon, then glares at Reese.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She punches him soundly on the shoulder and storms off.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: At this moment she is bowled over by an IRISH SETTER that licks her face while she shrieks with laughter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese seems about to smile but doesn't quite know how to go about it.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 191 EXT. SERVICE STATION/PAY PHONE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah is talking on an open pay phone.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: ...I know, Mom.
{DIALOGUE}: This is the soonest I could...I know.
{DIALOGUE}: Mom...Mom, I can't talk long.
{DIALOGUE}: No, I'm okay.
{META_DATA}: (pause)
{DIALOGUE}: I was on TV?
{DIALOGUE}: Really?
{META_DATA}: (pause)
{DIALOGUE}: Oh no, I hate that picture... why didn't you give them my graduation picture?
{META_DATA}: (pause)
{DIALOGUE}: I'm okay, really.
{DIALOGUE}: Listen, I want you to pack some stuff and go up to the cabin for a few days.
{DIALOGUE}: Just don't...no, don't ask any questions.
{DIALOGUE}: Just do it.
{DIALOGUE}: I gotta get going...gotta go.
{DIALOGUE}: Bye, bye.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah has been idly leafing through the DIRECTORY.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On a whim she looks up something.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She freezes for a moment when she finds the listing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then with a triumphant expression she rips the page out of the book.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 192 EXT. SERVICE STATION/PICNIC TABLE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah is sitting at a table under a tree, lettering something with a lipstick on a cardboard box-flap.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: E.C.U. - SIGN, as the last letters are finished.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It reads: SILICON VALLEY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FULL ON SARAH as she retracts the lipstick and leans across to hand it to a girl at the next table.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: Thanks a lot.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: What's that?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah looks up, startled to see him standing beside her.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: That's where we're going.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{DIALOGUE}: Why?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah point to the directory page lying on the table.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MACRO - PAGE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah's finger points to a listing which reads:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CYBER DYNAMICS CORPORATION
{DIALOGUE}: 18144 El Camino Real, S'Vale
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON SARAH AND REESE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She looks smug.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
