{DIALOGUE}: Isn't that it?
{DIALOGUE}: Cyber Dynamics Corporation?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{DIALOGUE}: What about it?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: Didn't you say that they're going to develop this revolutionary new thing...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{DIALOGUE}: Molecular-memory.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: Whatever...they become the hotshot computer guys so they get the job to build El Computer Grande...Skynet...for the government.
{DIALOGUE}: Right?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{META_DATA}: (uneasy)
{DIALOGUE}: That's the way it was told to me.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah's fear has been replaced by excitement.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: Well, we're gonna uninvent the bastard.
{DIALOGUE}: Eighty-six it.
{DIALOGUE}: We'll blow up the place...burn it down.
{DIALOGUE}: Something.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{META_DATA}: (very cold)
{DIALOGUE}: Tactically dangerous.
{DIALOGUE}: We lay low.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: Reese.
{DIALOGUE}: Think it through.
{DIALOGUE}: We can prevent the war.
{DIALOGUE}: Nobody else is gonna do it.
{DIALOGUE}: If we go to anybody official we wind up back in jail and then that walking cuisinart has got us again.
{DIALOGUE}: We have to so it ourselves.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{DIALOGUE}: That's not my mission.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{META_DATA}: (upset, mocking his manner)
{DIALOGUE}: Listen.
{DIALOGUE}: Understand.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm not a military objective, Reese.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm a person... You don't own me.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese takes her arm and pulls her to her feet.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{DIALOGUE}: Let's go.
{DIALOGUE}: Time to move out.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: Fuck you!
{DIALOGUE}: Let go of me!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She jerks her arm free.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He reaches for her again but she outdistances him, running.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{META_DATA}: (warning tone)
{DIALOGUE}: Sarah!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She dashes down a footpath among the trees, clutching her sign.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese follows her into the woods.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 193 EXT. WOODS/CLEARING - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Only a few yards from the picnic area, the woods take over completely.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PANNING WITH SARAH
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: as she runs down the path.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese tackles her from behind and they fall together in the long spring grass.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She struggles violently to get away.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: Let...go...bastard...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She gets one arm free and whacks him hard in the face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese reacts instinctively, leaping back in a defensive crouch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah freezes when she sees the .357 in his hand.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: (continuing, scared, but angry) Oh, that's real smart.
{DIALOGUE}: Go on, shoot me.
{DIALOGUE}: That's brilliant.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese is trembling as he lowers the gun.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah too is shaking with emotion.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tears roll down her cheeks and her voice cracks.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: Jesus Christ, Reese.
{DIALOGUE}: Can't you see I'm scared?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He straightens up and his arms go limp at his sides.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns away.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: I can't spend my life waiting for that thing to catch up with me...always looking over my shoulder, wondering if I left some tiny clue behind...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese doesn't respond.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The gun slips from his fingers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His will seems to drain from him and he sags to his knees.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The moment stretches.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There is only the sunlight moving in shafts through the leaves, the sound of a small stream nearby, birds chirping.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: Reese?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She crawls over to him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: C.U. - REESE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: in profile, with Sarah in B.G. His eyes are closed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A tear meanders down his cheek.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{META_DATA}: (continuing, quietly)
{DIALOGUE}: Kyle?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{META_DATA}: (a whisper)
{DIALOGUE}: I'm wrong here.
{DIALOGUE}: I wasn't meant to see this...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He gestures at their surroundings.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: It's...like some dream.
{DIALOGUE}: This...this...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He touches the grass, the trunk of a tree.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: ...and you...all so...beauti- ful.
{DIALOGUE}: It hurts, Sarah.
{DIALOGUE}: More than death.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks are her beseechingly.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
