{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 210 INT. MOTEL ROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A heartwarming domestic scene.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah and Kyle have pulled the dresser out to use as a worktable.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pans, packages and bottles clutter the kitchen, B.G. On the table between them are eight ten-inch lengths of PLUMBER'S PIPE, threaded each end.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kyle is showing Sarah how to tamp the HIGH-EXPLOSIVE PUTTY into the pipe bombs and seal them shut.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{DIALOGUE}: Make sure there's none on the threads, like this.
{DIALOGUE}: Now screw the end-cap on...very gently.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: You must have had a fun child- hood.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{DIALOGUE}: That's good.
{DIALOGUE}: Now, seven more like that while I make fuses.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: I was thinking, there's so much I've got to show you when we get through this.
