{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: I want to buy you a hot dog so bad,Kyle...all the things you've never seen and done.
{DIALOGUE}: You're here, but wherever you go, and whatever you touch, you bring the war with you.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{DIALOGUE}: My whole life has been combat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: I want it to be over for you.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{DIALOGUE}: Not possible.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: I want it to be over for me too.
{DIALOGUE}: I feel like I slipped over some invisible line, that I'm in your world now.
{DIALOGUE}: Everything's the same, but I see it differently.
{DIALOGUE}: It's like, there's you and me, and him...but nobody else can understand or help or even touch us.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese looks up and finally catches her gaze.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He reaches out for her hand and it seems he may be taking it to comfort her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But he turns her wrist to read her watch.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{DIALOGUE}: We'll head out at 0200.
{DIALOGUE}: That gives you four hours to sleep if you want.
{DIALOGUE}: I'll finish.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 211 INT. MOTEL ROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE ON TABLE - The bombs are neatly ranked, finished.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A nylon satchel lies nearby.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The mess is cleaned up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WIDE SHOT reveals Reese sitting in silent vigil at the window.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The room is dark, lit only by a streetlight outside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah is asleep on the bed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese sits cross-legged, shirtless, his body held rigid.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The image of discipline.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The .357 is held loosely in one hand on his lap.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There is a fresh bandage on his shoulder.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah wakes up and goes to him in the darkness.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks at her for a moment as she sits beside him, then back outside.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: He'll find us, won't he?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{DIALOGUE}: Probably.
{DIALOGUE}: Sarah, if I get zeroed...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: Don't say that.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{DIALOGUE}: If I do, you have to get away, disappear without a trace.
{DIALOGUE}: Different country, different name, everything.
{DIALOGUE}: In case they send another one.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: It'll never be over, will it?
{DIALOGUE}: Look at me, I'm shaking.
{DIALOGUE}: Some legend, huh?
{DIALOGUE}: You must be pretty disappointed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm not.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Several beats before Sarah speaks again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her eyes seem luminous in the dark.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{META_DATA}: (softly)
{DIALOGUE}: Kyle, the women in your time...what were they like?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{DIALOGUE}: Good fighters.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: That's not what I meant.
{DIALOGUE}: Was there someone special?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{DIALOGUE}: Someone?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: A girl.
{DIALOGUE}: You know.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{META_DATA}: (mechanically)
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{META_DATA}: (pause)
{DIALOGUE}: Never.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks away, outside the window
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{META_DATA}: (softly)
{DIALOGUE}: I'm sorry.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah studies him for a moment.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She's sitting slightly behind him and she puts her hands on his shoulders and back, tracing the lines of his scars with her fingertips.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: So much pain.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{DIALOGUE}: Pain can be controlled.
{DIALOGUE}: You disconnect it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: And so you feel nothing.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{DIALOGUE}: It's better that way.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{META_DATA}: (with great sympathy)
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, Kyle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese takes a long, slow breath before he answers, and when he does his voice has a new quality, an unfamiliar tenderness.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{DIALOGUE}: John Connor gave me a picture of you once.
{DIALOGUE}: I never knew why.
{DIALOGUE}: It was very old.
{DIALOGUE}: Torn.
{DIALOGUE}: Faded.
{DIALOGUE}: You were young, like you are now.
{DIALOGUE}: You weren't smiling...just a little sad... I always wondered what you were thinking at that second.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He closes his eyes, reaches toward her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His fingertips trace the contour of her nose, chin, cheeks.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: I memorized every line, every curve...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He opens his eyes, looking right at hers.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: Sarah, I came across time for you.
{DIALOGUE}: I love you.
{DIALOGUE}: I always have.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah is quietly overwhelmed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese looks away.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: I'm sorry.
{DIALOGUE}: I shouldn't have said...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: Kyle...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She leans forward and kisses him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His face is frozen.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A mask.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She continues, tenderly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He begins to respond.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The dam breaks and he holds her in a tight, trembling embrace, clinging to her like life itself.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kyle picks her up and carries her to the bed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She kisses his neck and chest, tracing his scars with her lips.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He unbuttons her blouse very slowly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah guides his powerful hands over her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A SEQUENCE OF CUTS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DETAILS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IMPRESSIONS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah, a very close angle, as she grimaces in divine agony.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese, his face rapt.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His hand, clutching the pillow as if to kill it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is explosive, torrential.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A confluence of fate and will.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 212 INT. MOTEL ROOM/LATER - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TIGHT ON SARAH AND REESE in each other's arms.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lying across his chest, she surveys his face as his eyes close drowsily.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: I bet you're ticklish.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{META_DATA}: (uncompre- hending)
{DIALOGUE}: Ticklish?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah's hand moves OUT OF FRAME.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: After a moment Reese looks down, puzzled.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{DIALOGUE}: What are you doing?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{META_DATA}: (continuing doggedly)
{DIALOGUE}: You'll beg for mercy in a second.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese seems unperturbed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Finally he begins to squirm.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{DIALOGUE}: I don't think I like this.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: You're not supposed to.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Now Reese is becoming desperate.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A grimace spreads across his face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It becomes a grin.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then he's laughing, trying to escape but she won't let him, and they collapse, laughing together.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah gazes at his grin, a glimpse of the Reese that might have been, in another life.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A moment later the grin vanishes at the sound of dogs barking outside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese is off the bed in an instant, crouched tense, eyes alert.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Feral as ever.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{META_DATA}: (whispering)
{DIALOGUE}: Listen to the dogs.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 213 EXT. MOTEL OFFICE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The German Shepherd, barking furiously, LUNGES TOWARD CAMERA repeatedly, at the end of a chain.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A dark figure moves by in the F.G., out of the dog's reach.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 214/FX INT./EXT. MOTEL/TERMINATOR'S POV - NIGHT 214/FX
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The digitized view is image-intensified, bright and stark as a lunar landscape.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PAN OFF the lunging dog to the row of rooms facing the parking lot.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HANDHELD as we approach the doors.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is WIDE ANGLE and the barrel of the AR-180 is visible at the bottom of FRAME.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The nearest vehicle parked in front is a LARGE PICKUP TRUCK WITH TWO DIRT BIKES lashed in the bed, seen prominently as we pass.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The POV approaches a door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Number 14.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The door is KICKED OPEN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Moving inside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The assault rifle sprays the room, exploding the indistinct forms on the bed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Staccato glare.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Approaching the bed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nothing there put the shredded remain of sheets and pillows.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The POV shifts to the BACK DOOR, which is ajar, and moves toward it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Through the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Revealing an EMPTY YARD.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 215 INT. PICKUP TRUCK/PARKING LOT - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese is under the dash, playing with the wires.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah lies on the seat, clutching the nylon satchel, which bulges with the explosive charges.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She has dressed hastily and is barefoot.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{DIALOGUE}: Light it now.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah has been holding a BIC LIGHTER near the tip of a fuse.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She thumbs the flame on.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The fuse catches as Reese twists the wires and the engine starts to turn over.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 216 INT./EXT. MOTEL ROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator spins at the sound of the truck engine catching.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FAST PANAGLIDE WITH HIM as he runs the length of the suite, stops outside the front door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Whips the AR to his shoulder.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The truck is BACKING WILDLY across the lot B.G. Terminator turns, looking into CAMERA as a SIZZLING SOUND becomes audible.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DETAIL - PIPE CHARGE, lying just inside the door, in the shadows.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The fuse is burning.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WIDE SHOT - On doorway, from the parking lot, as Terminator takes two leaping strides forward and the CHARGE EXPLODES.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The front of the building is BLOWN TO KINDLING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator is flung forward by the blast.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 217 EXT. STREET/PICKUP TRUCK - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PANNING RAPIDLY as the truck shoots out of the parking lot and tears down the street.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 218 EXT. MOTEL - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator lies face down, motionless, F.G., as the debris from the blast settles.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A YOUNG GUY ON A HONDA 750 crosses the parking lot and stops near him, running forward.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator starts to get up, moving slowly.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RIDER
{META_DATA}: (crouching be- side him)
{DIALOGUE}: Don't try to move, buddy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MOVING WITH TERMINATOR as he shoves the cyclist aside and approaches the BIKE, which is STILL RUNNING.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 219/FX PARKING LOT/TERMINATOR'S POV - NIGHT 219/FX
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Digitized POV, approaching the cycle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The image reduces to GRAPHIC OUTLINES, with separate systems COLOR-CODED.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It breaks down suddenly into individual SIDE, TOP and PLAN VIEWS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: All in less than four seconds.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 220 INT./EXT. FREEWAY/PICKUP TRUCK - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese slides the truck into an ON-RAMP and guns in onto the freeway, burying the throttle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Traffic is light...a few 18-wheelers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The truck tops out at 110 and he holds it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They flicker rapidly through pools of light and shadow.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE OVER REESE'S SHOULDER as they hurtle forward.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An interchange flashes by in an instant.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PACING WITH THE TRUCK, looking back as a single headlight arcs radically across all lanes behind them and grows BRIGHTER, CLOSING.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 221 EXT. FREEWAY - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LOW WIDE ANGLE preceding Terminator on the bike.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is tucked, getting as much speed as possible out of the 750.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As he GAINS ON THE CAMERA, FILLING FRAME, he unslings the assault rifle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Raises it against the windstream in a one- handed pistol grip.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 222 INT. PICKUP TRUCK - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese motions Sarah to keep her head down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pulls the Colt Python from his coat pocket.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Steering with his elbows, he checks the load.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Snaps the cylinder shut.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Glances in the rear mirror.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Turns the wheel.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 223 EXT. FREEWAY - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WIDE ANGLE, following close to Terminator, as he closes on the pickup, B.G.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The truck swerves suddenly, diving around a TRACTOR-TRAILER.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator leans hard to follow.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LOW WIDE ANGLE preceding the pickup and Terminator as they swerve as high speed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese uses the slow semis as static obstacles.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He misses them by inches, TIRES SQUEALING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE OVER SARAH'S SHOULDER, through the front window as the back of a SEMI-TRAILER hurtles toward them, straight ahead.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HIGH ANGLE, following both vehicles as Reese feints RIGHT and then skids LEFT.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He slides toward the trailer in a FOUR-WHEEL DRIFT as Terminator commits to the right.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: M.C.U. - TERMINATOR, over the barrel of the AR, as he FIRES.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SIDE ANGLE - PASSING TRUCK-TRAILER, bullets strafe across it as the pickup vanishes behind.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator skids the bike, barely missing an abutment, and is forced onto an OFF-RAMP.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LOW SIDE ANGLE preceding Terminator as he roars down the off-ramp without slowing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Runs the red light at the bottom as a hundred miles an hour.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Climbs the ON-RAMP.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 224 INT. PICKUP TRUCK - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah is buffeted as Reese fights to control the skidding truck.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The angle is past Reese, F.G., on Sarah.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator appears B.G., converging rapidly as the on-ramp joins the freeway.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: REESE
{DIALOGUE}: Switch places with me.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She slides over him while he keeps the hammer down.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 225 EXT. FREEWAY - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese is out the window to the waist, aiming double- handed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He FIRES.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ONCE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TWICE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: AGAIN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They enter an interchange.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ahead lies a LONG, SWEEPING CURVE, two lanes wide and elevated.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator rocks back from a round between the eyes that bares metal, the FIRES.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bullets rake the pickup.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The windows are blown out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The side mirror explodes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reese is hit.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Drops the .357.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah screams and weaves, barely in control.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 226 INT. PICKUP TRUCK - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah reaches across and pulls Reese's limp body back inside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He slumps on the seat, moaning.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stunned.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: Kyle...oh God...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He has a bullet in the chest.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Another has broken his arm.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah feels all hope recede.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 227 EXT. FREEWAY - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator crosses behind the truck, coming up on Sarah's side.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He FIRES.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah shrieks as the doorpost next to her head CLANGS WITH HITS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The short burst EMPTIES THE GUN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It CLATTERS TO THE PAVEMENT a moment later, discarded.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator draws the .38.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Takes aim.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah SCREAMS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HITS THE BREAKS HARD.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CRANKS THE WHEEL.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: GLASS behind her EXPLODES with gunfire.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SWERVING VICIOUSLY the truck SLAMS THE BIKE, sending it FLYING INTO A GUARDRAIL.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator goes over the handle bars at a hundred miles per hour.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 228 INT. PICKUP TRUCK - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah fights the wheel, losing control of the slewing pickup.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 229 EXT. FREEWAY OVERPASS - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator hits the pavement, tumbling, rolling, sliding with a CHATTERING SCREECH and spraying sheets of SPARKS as flesh strips away and steel screams on concrete.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The pickup SWAPS ENDS violently, smashing into the guardrail.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator hits the guardrail, bounces up, tumbles along the top and then pitches OUT INTO SPACE.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 230 EXT. INTERSECTING FREEWAY - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator smashes to the pavement in the middle lane and lies there, face-down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Still.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 231 INT./EXT. PICKUP/OVERPASS - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah is slammed hard as the truck grinds to a stop against the guardrail.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She checks Kyle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is barely conscious.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah heaves open the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Runs to the guardrail.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Looks down.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 232 EXT. LOWER FREEWAY - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: After a long moment Terminator slowly rolls over and sits up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LOW ANGLE as he rises into FRAME, a mass of blood.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clothing and skin in tatters.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HEADLIGHTS FLARE behind him and an AIRHORN BLARES.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FULL SHOT as a DOUBLE-TRAILER KENWORTH GASOLINE TANKER smashes him down and under with a METALLIC CRASH.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANGLE UNDER TANKER as Terminator rolls, clattering, and the mass blurs above him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He RICOCHETS between the pavement and the speeding undercarriage until a stray bounce flings him up into the rear suspension.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 233 EXT. FREEWAY OVERPASS - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: UP ANGLE ON SARAH
