{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TILT UP to follow her gaze.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The sign above the entrance of the building reads:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CYBER DYNAMICS CORPORATION
{META_DATA}: SLOW DISSOLVE TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 259 INT./EXT. LANDROVER - LATE AFTERNOON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MACRO ON CASSETTE RECORDER, the center capstans of a tape turning.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: ...and the hardest thing is deciding what I should tell you and what not to.
{DIALOGUE}: Well, anyway, I've got a while yet before you're old enough to understand the tapes.
{DIALOGUE}: They're more for me at this point... to help get it all straight.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: COVER SHOT reveals Sarah as the wheel of a dusty landrover parked at the pump island of a tiny gas station.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: All of its signs are in hand-lettered Spanish.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beyond lies an expanse of scrub desert.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The sky scowls with an impending storm.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah speaks quietly into a hand microphone as a dark- complected attendant laconically fills her tank.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She cradles the cassette recorder in her lap, in the lee of her SWOLLEN BELLY.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She looks to be about SIX MONTHS ALONG.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Under her down vest she wears a leather shoulder holster and the butt of a .357 REVOLVER presses against her breast.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She tugs the vest closed as the attendant glances her way.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A German Shepherd sits in the back among taped boxes and suitcases.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: Should I tell you about your father?
{DIALOGUE}: That's a tough one.
{DIALOGUE}: Will it change your decision to send him here...knowing?
{DIALOGUE}: But if you don't send Kyle, you could never be.
{DIALOGUE}: God, you can go crazy thinking about all this...I suppose I'll tell you...I owe him that.
{DIALOGUE}: And maybe it'll be enough if you know that in the few hours we had together we loved a lifetime's worth...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLICK.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WHIR.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah jumps at a sound nearby, breaking her reverie.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A small MEXICAN BOY has snapped her picture with a beat-up Polaroid camera.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He holds it out to her, speaking rapid Spanish.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ATTENDANT
{DIALOGUE}: He says you are very beautiful, Senora, and he is ashamed to ask five American dollars for this picture, but if he does not, his father will beat him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: That's a pretty good hustle, kid.
{DIALOGUE}: Four.
{DIALOGUE}: Quatro.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The boy takes her four dollars and she watches the snapshot develop.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is a good photograph of her, the wind lightly ruffling her hair, expression thought- ful, slightly sad.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We recognize it as the one Reese carried in 2029.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She slips it into her short pocket.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ATTENDANT
{DIALOGUE}: Mil trescientos...fifteen dollars American.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As she pays him, distant thunder rolls.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The boy yells something in Spanish as he runs off.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: What did he say?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ATTENDANT
{META_DATA}: (accented)
{DIALOGUE}: There is a storm coming in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah gazes at the thunderheads building up out over the desert.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Heat lightning pulses in their depths.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{META_DATA}: (quietly)
{DIALOGUE}: I know.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CAMERA CRANES UP as she pulls away, driving across the flat desert on a ribbon of highway.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A brilliant flash crescendos from horizon to horizon out at the rim of the world.
